# No Inline JSDoc in Object Types

Never place `/** ... */` JSDoc comments inline inside object type literals. Always expand to multi-line.

```typescript
// ❌ BAD
options: { /** Logger instance */ logger: Logger }
nodes: { /** Token */ token: string }[]
title: { /** ID */ id: string; /** Default message */ defaultMessage: string }

// ✅ GOOD
options: {
  /** Logger instance */
  logger: Logger;
}
nodes: {
  /** Token */
  token: string;
}[]
title: {
  /** ID */
  id: string;
  /** Default message */
  defaultMessage: string;
}
```

This applies to inline types in function parameters, interface properties, and generic type arguments alike.
